cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it focuses on the dissemination and evolution of information in online social networks. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) as it mentions the transfer of text sequences between different memes. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it discusses the implications of understanding the mechanism driving change in diffusing information. It may also fall under cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) as it analyzes the behavior of social networks. Finally, it could be classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it examines the replication and evolution of text sequences in memes.
